Laura Robson took the opportunity to cool down in the Florida heat on Thursday while she dipped in an ice bath as the British tennis nears a return to action after more than a year off the court.

The 21-year-old has not played since the 2014 Australian Open more than 15 months ago after requiring surgery on an injured wrist.

But Robson, who has been training in Tampa in a bid to build up her fitness in time to take part in next month's French Open at Roland Garros.

